  <h2>Conclusion: A Plan Beats Panic</h2>
  <p>The only way to make the right decisions in every phase of the first 24 hours is to have <strong>already made those decisions in advance</strong>. Create your family disaster plan today: determine your meeting point, contact person, and assembly area; prepare your earthquake kit and put it somewhere everyone knows. For a family that knows what to do in an earthquake, these 24 hours are not chaos — they are a plan, executed step by step.</p>
